caption: Fantastic fish sandwich
Great experience!  Loved the food,  vibe and music playlist!  Will be back soon!

Place was busy but great! Clam Chowder was AMAZING. We ate the fish tacos and calamari and general tso’s cauliflower. All very good. Beers were unique. Great Covid friendly patio situation. Thank you to our care taker Topher!
Seamores is a great spot! Service was a little slow but they were extremely busy so it is expected. The food and drinks were great!
The food came quickly, the server was attentive & the ambience of the place is warm, safe and spacious. This one is a hidden gem I had no idea was near me. I love this place and I love their food!
Upbeat atmosphere and friendly staff! The steelhead burger was delish-delish!

My friend and I went here the first night inside dining re-opened and were pleasantly surprised. We had a great table and every one was separated by dividers. We got the spicy tuna poke and shrimp nachos as apps and they were so delicious - i'm not a fan of sashimi but the tuna was very fresh and tasty.  I got the lobster mac and my friend got the lobster roll. both very tasty and the drinks were good as well.  The team was working together very efficiently and if someone was busy, there was always someone else willing to help. The location is nice too
The food was amazing. Lobster mac and cheese was my favorite.

I frequent this unique restaurant often since I like the good mood that is characterizes this restaurant. The staff is extraordianrillyremarkably cordial and well trained. The service is exceptionally fast. Also, the food they cook is outstanding. I have been there many times and I was always happy. The pay is reasobable. I suggest this restaurant to my friends and family.
So good! The seating is nice, the food, the space. Just not enough heaters.

Ray, Andrew and Omar took great care of us. Well poured drinks and tasty food. I even asked if they could heat my tea up in the microwave and they kindly let me know that they do not have a microwave in the resturant...everything is always fresh and cooked to order and it sure does taste like it! We'll be back for sure.

Good selection of fresh fish dishes plus some interesting and quirky dishes like the General Tso's Cauliflower appetizer. Good seating outdoor with overhead cover, yet plenty of space between patrons for a quick meal.
(Translated by Google) Very good food at reasonable prices  (Original) Muy buena la comida a precios razonable

I had a deplorable and disgusting experience earlier today when I walked in to pick up my takeout order. When I entered the restaurant one of the staff members who was a woman rushed to the door and said I can’t step in because of COVID regulations for the day.  There were two people eating at a table and also a customer at the bar. I kindly stated to her that I am here to pick up my takeout order. This woman was extremely rude to me. I felt discriminated against because of the hue of my skin. (If you know what I mean) I have dined at Seamore’s Bowery several times and received wonderful service. However,I will never patronage the Seamore’s Dumbo location EVER again. I will be sure to share my experience with many people. I’m so appalled.
They don't have a lot of variety and they food could use a lil more flavor
Good food.

I had lunch here with a friend of mine. I had been here once before and not been super impressed.  the fact is Dumbo has a lot of great eateries.  However this day, due to the pandemic, every other spot i could think of was closed.  I had not expected this.  Fortunately Seamore's was open and the two of us sat down across from each other and took our masks off.  My friend asked if what we were doing was risky.  At first i did not know what he meant and he explained that we had our masks off and were sitting across a table from each other and were much closer than 6 feet.  We decided not to dwell on that and proceeded to order.  A very sweet and chipper hostess took our order and when my friend asked what kind of clam chowder they were serving  and the hostess answered New England - i knew that was what i wanted.  to say the least it was one of the best clam chowders i've had in a long time.  Just full of flavor.   I also had a kale and avocado salad and a terrific catch up converstion with my friend and enjoyed both immensly.
One of my go-to spots to eat. awesome location, well organised, and fantastic customer service. Highly recommended!

I use to to right by Seamores and would go often with friends. The food is delicious and service always fast and friendly. I have talked to the owner a few times and he is super friendly and hard working it seems.
Bummed my mussels were pretty cold when served. But the fries were almost warm. Kind of a big bummer since I know how good the food is, but who wants to eat cold/room temp food?!
Amazing food and service! Lobster roll is the best I ever had! Service super friendly and attentive! Thank you so much.
Customer service above and beyond!  Monica, the hostess, should be the model on how to be the front person for all restaurants.  She made you feel that you were the VIP of the night.
Had a nice experience here a couple weeks ago. Mostly just had drinks. The General Tso's cauliflower was tasty. Quincey served us and was very friendly and knew the menu well.

The food was really good, General Tso's cauliflower,  Poke Tuna bowl. Oysters were fresh, but rather small for being $3 per piece. But it was all irrelevant to absolutely mind blowing mac and cheese and Reel Deal main course!  Also they Lobster Eggs Benedict looked very tempting!  So all in all, nice place and would recommend it to anyone.

Absolutely bad experience from staff, I ordered Beef burger and they give me Salmon Burger, so I told the server for her mistake because she will never came back to us to tell us about it, anyways I was ok I am nice girl and I eaten my  food, but “surprise” they charge me  “Peregrino water” that I didn’t ordered...  I ask for my check and no organization in this place.  Omar the “manager” was very disrespectful with me and me friend and feel discriminated cause his make fun of us cause our accent.  Insane staff.

Absolutely didn’t worth the experience, food was ok, didn’t worth the experience. First the staff absolutely have no clue what is on menu, when we did order, they didn’t get it right, there was no apology, and we got overcharged, and when we asked for bill, manager-supervisor Omar  said he can’t provided to us because he didn’t have printer.  Clearly manager Omar don’t have any idea how to manage situations like this, he has an  attitude when he was talking to us, he was making fun of our accent, he was trying to make a point we got drunk from drinking 2 glasses of wine. Everything was terrible from the beginning.

Good food, great location and service by Monica.  The burrito bowl is a great healthy lunch option on a great place. The fish and chips were ok and the cauliflower was order by every other table around us.  Overall the other employees could be more cordial and welcoming and understand the menu better, but the food is good and the location is great.
This place is amazing and the service rocks!!!

Recently went here with my girlfiend for my bday and was very disappointed. The outdoor seating is decent with the lighting setup they had. A bit cramped on the side walk but its not their fault. The best part of our meal was the cauliflower appetizer and my gf drink (I think it was called frose;) but other than that it was subpar. Took our waiter a while to take our order and while he was taking our order, he wasn't writing anything down and i could tell a mistake was going to be made. We received our food much after others that came in after us and when we did my gf received the wrong order. I ordered the Montauk scallops and my girl got the blackened shrimp. While the entrees was presented well and tasted decent, the portion size was off and was missing some type of sauce to bring it all together, not to mention that my gfs shrimp was wildly overcooked. It was borderline closing time so we just took our Ls. Pretty certain I won't be returning.

Great service as always resonable prices it shouldn't be no reason you can't stop by and pick up some fish and chips or how about the General Tsos Cauliflower one of my favorites guaranteed any vegetarian would love. Outdoor seating very nice Hilda is on the job always attentive and took great care of my party of five will being going back for the extremely generous service plus the delicous food 😀
Excellent food , I had the fish tacos I really recommend that . Staff friendly , you can eat outside They have tables . Pet friendly

Nice and cozy spot. I’m glad they adopted the outdoors area during pandemic - good and drinks are served in plastic cups and takeout tupperware. Digital menu is also convenient. Food itself is pretty tasty , highly recommend poke bowl- it’s huge and delicious. Prices are reasonable for the area . Overall 5 stars , had a good time there
Lots of fun; great service!

was walking around the area and was looking for a place to eat. saw seamore's and looked at the menu. grabbed 2 seats at the bar. staff was extremely friendly, interior spacious and colorful. had a bloody mary and the chipotle chicken burrito bowl. next time i visit NYC/Brooklyn i would like to go back to seamore's. only regret i have is that i didn't take a photo of my order in order to post here so you people can actually see it, but if youre in the area and love seafood, you should stop by and if the food doesn't appeal, at least sit at the bar and get yourself a drink!

Two of my friends and I came to this Seamore Sunday 12/23 @ 2pm to celebrate a friend's graduation. We thought this location would be better to avoid the chaos in Manhattan. The food was good but the service was not that great. Yes we were there for about 2 hours but we live busy lives and wanted to catch up. I have a background of working in a restaurant while working on my MA a few years but my friends do not. In our opinion (and my expert opinion) the waiter needs to be retrained. Our waitress was not attentive and slightly rude and drop everything on the table, proper placement would have been nice. I would have given this place a 4 or 5 b.c. of scene, location and food (which needed a little more seasoning) but unfortunately she ruined our experience. Hire new waitresses that care about their job and want to provide a good experience. We still tipped her but she didn't get nearly what we originally planned to give her.
Good reliable seafood with reasonable prices. Food was better than the service!
Soo delicious! Not over crowd, and amazing service
Excellent food, staff, service. Will definitely be back.

The food is horrible and overpriced. Great location, bad food. The ambiance is fair. The customer service is outstanding. Gave 1 star because the food is the reason to walk in the doors. Great service, great food

I went to see a play at St. Ann's Warehouse and decided to grab dinner before the show. I'm very glad that we popped into Seamore's. Their $1 oysters were delicious. My blue fish was excellent and my wife loved her poke bowl.  If you're in the neighborhood definitely try this restaurant out.
Great burger and salad.
Superb Lobster Mac and cheese
I’ve lived in NYC for over 10 years and this is possibly one of the worst meals I’ve ever had.

Wow - just awful. I didn’t know what Mahi Mahi would taste like if you microwaved it, but I do now (not saying they actually microwaved it, but they managed to get the effect). A tomato and cucumber salad had all of one half of a cherry tomato. And - let me just say that fresh fish doesn’t smell “fishy” - this place does not in a good way. I have an idea for sustainability of our oceans - close this place down.
Great vibe and menu...as someone who is a little picky about fish it's sometimes hit or miss based on the catch of the day but there are plenty of other great options otherwise.

I always enjoy coming here whenever I am in the area. There is often very little wait for a seat, the food is good & the service can not be beat, the genuinely seem to enjoy their job  which is rare these days.  Ihave never had a poor experience here.

Yummy seafood, fresh beers on tap, and the service is always good by the friendly and knowledgeable staff. Don’t know what the other reviewers are on about. Love this place - great addition to the neighborhood!

Had some great food, spirits, and service. Enjoy!

Been twice. After it opened and then several months later, but the experience was the same - dreadful. I've had better meals at Ikea, seriously. The menu is so basic that you have to wonder whether it is devised with a trainee kirchen in mind (fish from A, sides from B). Despite this fool proof set-up the food never arrives, no matter if they are full or empty. Ravenous by this point, tears well up in your eyes as you are greeted to weightwatcher sized portions of over cooked fish, revolting dressing, and a sprinkle of sad veg. SweetGreens and Westville around the corner are gourmet by comparison. The acoustics are awful, so it is frighteningly loud with voices. Saw a manager the first night only and staff looks young. There is a demand for casual seafood restaurants, but it's hard to understand how any of the Seamores outposts stay in business if they are all this bad. Had real hopes for this addition to the neighborhood, but sadly I won't return.
A great happy hour. The oysters are amazing.
The food and service were amazing. Would recommend to everyone I know

This place was excellent! The food/fish combo special was plenty for one person without ordering apps. I want to go back and try the other dishes though. Atmosphere is very open spaced and feels very comfortable and not tightly compact.

This quaint little DUMBO treasure plays host to FIFA 2018, and some of the cities most up and coming Millennial patrons.  Join the  crowd (Down Under the Manhattan Bridge Overpass). Ask for Esther.... (wink)

Very quick service and the food was excellent. I ordered the Reel Deal, which is a good value at just $24 for a whole lot of food - they don’t skimp on the 3 sides that come with your fish. My boyfriend got the shrimp tacos which were also awesome. Everything tasted fresh. Docking one star because we ordered oysters and they never came, and the squash was a little underdone, but everything else was so good that we didn’t mind and will definitely eat here again.

If was so delicious. Also came with THREE sides. So much food and Mac n Cheese was awesome as well as the Farro. Must go.

Yuuuum yum yummy grub is an understatement. I came here because of a partnership they had with The Wing Dumbo so naturally I went IN. The breadcrumbs on the clam pasta alone will have you licking your plate, the gumbo was flavorful and the curry was light which was nicer than expected. Something to note: it’s a quality seafood spot along the Dumbo waterfront so prices definitely reflect that
